result.execSummary:
The defendant Rafael Gonzales was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Case Called @ 3:24 PM: Defendant Rafael Gonzales in court with attorney Jeffrey Allen Mann.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Agreement recited by DA.  Def and counsel concur with recital.  Per DA:  Def remains on supervision at this time, no further supervision being requested.    Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea:  Court accepts plea and enters JOC.  Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed - no response from victim - victim's mother present in courtroom.  Court accepts State's Motion to Amend Ct 1 to DC w/Dom Abuse Enh contrary to 947.01 Plea:  NC  Plea Ct 2 (POP):   NC  Court accepts pleas and enters JOC.  Ct 3 DRI.  Statement by victim's mother.  Statement by Def:  None offered.  The Court:  Accepts resolution and will honor the same.  Recogizes that supervision is currently in place.  Each Count - Court Costs imposed - 60 DTP or PP.  Ct Appt Atty Fees imposes - bill to be submitted by the end of the week.  Appeal Rights Given.  3 days TS credit granted.
from DE to the Court - Unable to supply the full $250 deposit ordered for Ct Appt Counsel - the Court will address at the next hearing

2:58 pm case called. Defendant Rafael Gonzales in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant wishes to have an attorney represent him and was just released from jail-requests 30 days to obtain counsel. Court questions discussion with DA. Statement by defendant-requests bond modification. Court requires by April 10, 2015 defendant to pay $250.00 and commencing June 1, 2015 payments of $50.00 per month towards attorney fees. Court will appoint an attorney.    Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State and probable cause finding as to each count alleged within the complaint. Court denies request for bond modification.   Status conference scheduled for May 1, 2015 at 03:30 pm.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.

Case called @ 1:10 p.m. Defendant Rafael Gonzales in court, in custody, appears via video with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel. Defendant will be not be represented by SPD if released from custody. ADA Anderson requesting $2500 Sig Bond. Atty Szilagyi takes no position as to bond. Court orders $2500 Sig Bond. IA Scheduled - NOH Given.  Riverside Ruling in favor of the State.  Initial appearance scheduled for April 2, 2015 at 03:00 pm.
